    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - DIAGNOSTIC TOOLS AND ACCESSORIES - Tools and Accessories - IPR
        Isolation Adapter
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>IPR Isolation Adapter</title>
        <figure id="f2400826" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="IPR_isolation_adapter" filename="../figD31/D3190.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                     scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>ZTSE4605</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The IPR isolation adapter is used to pressurize the ICP system to test the system's integrity without the
            influence of the IPR valve. Install the adapter into the back of the high pressure pump cover to block off
            the high pressure oil flow (control) to the IPR valve. If IPR valve leaks, replace the IPR valve.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
